$ Oracle: init parameter PARALLEL_DEGREE_POLICY
@ parallel_degree_policy

`parallel_degree_policy` determines the policy used to compute the *degree of parallelism*.

The value cna be set to `MANUAL`, `LIMITED`, `AUTO` or `ADAPTIVE`.

When `parallel_degree_policy` is set to `auto`, Oracle will queue the
→ development/databases/Oracle/SQL/statement/execution[execution of SQL statements] that require
→ development/databases/Oracle/SQL/statement/execution/parallel[parallel execution] if the necessary number of parallel execution servers
is not available.

sa:
  → development/databases/Oracle/adminstration/init-parameters

